<p>GDP growth: -3.5% GDP: $200bn (PPP: $292bn) Inflation: 1.0% Population: 11.3m GDP per head: $17,710 (PPP: $25,820)</p>

<p>Europe's heavyweights are determined to preserve the single currency, so will attempt to keep Greece upright by hook or by crook until its debt can be restructured in an orderly way that does not destroy the euro. The country is insolvent in all but name, trapped between the Scylla of austerity and the Charybdis of violent protest. It has become harder and harder for the government to steer a steady course. Regardless of who governs, the economy will plummet—more quickly and deeply outside the euro zone than in. </p>

